Objective

Define a structured, sprint-based implementation roadmap for delivering the cloud-native download processing feature with controlled scope and measurable outcomes.


1 Sprint 1: Architecture & API Definition

1.1 Goals
-Finalize service boundaries
-Define API contracts
-Validate functional and non-functional requirements
-Align stakeholders on scope

1.2 Deliverables
-Approved API specification
-Architecture diagram
-MVP scope confirmation
-Risk identification summary

1.3 Acceptance Criteria
-API endpoints documented and reviewed
-Service interactions clearly defined
-Non-functional requirements validated

2 Sprint 2: Observability & Operational Readiness

2.1 Goals
-Define monitoring metrics
-Establish logging standards
-Design health check endpoints
-Define alerting thresholds

2.2 Deliverables
-Observability plan
-Alert criteria documentation
-Health endpoint specification

2.3 Acceptance Criteria
-Metrics mapped to business and system outcomes
-Alert triggers defined
-Health states documented

3 Sprint 3: Rollout & Risk Mitigation Planning

3.1 Goals
-Define staged rollout strategy
-Establish rollback criteria
-Document failure scenarios and mitigation paths
-Finalize deployment readiness checklist

3.2 Deliverables
-Rollout strategy document
-Rollback plan
-Risk classification matrix
-Deployment readiness checklist

3.3 Acceptance Criteria
-Rollback triggers clearly defined
-Mitigation steps documented
-Stakeholder communication plan prepared


4 Execution Principles
-Incremental delivery
-Early risk detection
-Continuous monitoring alignment
-Clear cross-functional communication


5 Product Owner Perspective

This sprint structure ensures:
-Controlled feature delivery
-Measurable progress
-Operational readiness before launch
-Reduced production risk

Structured planning supports predictable outcomes in cloud-native product environments.
